  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key aspects typically include:\n\n1. Required reporting of suspicious transactions\n2. Customer identification procedures\n3. Record-keeping requirements\n4. Monitoring financial activities\n5. Mandatory reporting of large cash transactions\n\nDifferent countries have their own specific AML laws, but many follow international standards set by organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF).",
